                                        <div class="story-body">
                                                <h2 class="headline">
                            <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/climate/winter-cold-weather.html" data-rref="">If the Earth Is Warming, Why Is It So Cold Outside?</a>
                        </h2>
                                                    <div class="thumb">
                                <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2019/climate/winter-cold-weather.html" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" tabindex="-1"  data-rref="">
                                    <img
                                        src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2019/01/28/climate/cli-winter-cold-weather/merlin_149760537_7d75e88a-b1cb-448e-8624-713678d9b263-thumbStandard.jpg"
                                        role="presentation"
                                        alt=""
                                    />
                                </a>
                            </div>
                                                <p class="summary">Even on a day when it is colder than average where you live, the world as a whole is frequently warmer than average. You can even see it for yourself.</p>
                        <p class="byline">
                            <span class="freshness"><time data-utc-timestamp="1548704424" datetime="1548704424"></time></span>
                                                            <span class="divider"></span>
